REPLACE INTO "events" VALUES (4,'campaign','1994-01-02','1994-01-02','','Youth Action Plan 1994-1996 - A People Friendlier Earth',NULL,'The aim of this action plan launched at the Life-Link conference in 1994, is to propose a project to be run in all Friendship-Schools for two years to develop a Youth Action Plan (YAP) on how the Human Rights situation on our planet can be improved and human security increase globally',NULL,NULL,NULL,'no');
REPLACE INTO "events" VALUES (5,'campaign','1996-01-01','1996-01-01','','Caring and Sharing for Our Future 1997-1998',NULL,'Global common security includes caring and sharing on three levels: Myself, My fellow citizens, Our Biology/Biosphere/Environment. The campaign will first ask schoos to work on any preferred topic within the dimensions of Human Rights and the Environment. Secondly, we want to have a description on how the project was planned, run and followed-up. Thirdly and finally, we want an analysis of what conflicts can arise from the topic studies. We will stress the awareness and training of early Conflict Resolution skills during this campaign.',NULL,NULL,NULL,'no');
REPLACE INTO "events" VALUES (6,'campaign','1998-01-01','1998-01-01','','Youth Caring and Sharing Actions at Schools Worldwide\r\n Year 2000',NULL,'Youth, age preferably 12-19 years old, in cooperation with teachers at more than 2000 schools worldwide are invited to come up with proposals on practical actions that could take place at schools during the year 2000. The proposals will be evaluated at the Life-Link international office in Uppsala, Sweden. \r\nBased on the proposals, 20 qualified schools will be invited to an international youth and schools conference, in Sigtuna, Sweden 1999, to conclude a \"Manual on Actions 2000+\". \r\nThe Manual on Actions 2000+ will be distributed to all participating schools as well as other joining schools worldwide',NULL,NULL,NULL,'no');
REPLACE INTO "events" VALUES (7,'campaign','1999-01-01','1999-01-01','','Launching Youth Caring and Sharing Actions at Schools Worldwide Year 2000+',NULL,'A campaign for the New Millenium was launched, based on the basic Life-Link ethics: Care and Share, Care for Myself - Care for Others - Care for Nature.\r\nA follow up conference was suggested for year 2001.',NULL,NULL,NULL,'no');
